  "text": "Those studies highlighted an advanced state of reproductive isolation between the races (expected by their highly divergent Robertonian karyotipic structures) and gave us the opportunity, especially using the population genetics parameters inferred by microsatellites, to correlate the genetic and morphological distances of the mice datasets, giving us more power to detect the karyotipic-induced shape variation. In fact, our analyses show that, when using the whole landmark configuration, the genetic and morphometric distances are significantly correlated, confirming the genetic bases underlying the mandible shape [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
